{"word":"διαπορέω","slug":"διαπορέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>διαπορέω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ήσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to be quite at a loss</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>:—so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, with <a href='S:aorist tense'>aor.</a> and <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to raise an</i> <el>ἀπορία</el>, <i>start a difficulty</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b>:—so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>: —<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be matter of doubt</i> or <i>question</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}